                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190707-25-victim288 t18190707-25-viclabel146"></join>, and lives in <placeName id="t18190707-25-crimeloc147">East-street, Finsbury-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18190707-25-crimeloc147" type="placeName" value="East-street, Finsbury-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18190707-25-crimeloc147" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190707-25-off144 t18190707-25-crimeloc147"></join>. On the 9th of June the prisoner came to the shop, and asked if I knew a man named Richardson? I said No. He then asked for Long-alley. I told him, and he went away. About half-past three o'clock I heard footsteps in the shop, got up, and missed the watch, which hung on a wire in the window. I ran out, turned the corner, and saw the prisoner - he was stopped, I asked him for the watch, he said he had not got it, but had laid it under a cart just by. It was produced soon after.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190707-25-person291">
